ck_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":33,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2010\/09\/15\/concealing-faults-baby-girl\/","url_meta":{"origin":25273,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Faults: Concealing character faults like saving baby girls","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 15, 2010","format":false,"excerpt":"'Uqbah ibn 'Amir reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cOne who sees a character flaw and conceals it is like one who revives a baby girl buried alive.\" Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 4891 Grade:\u00a0Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Suyuti \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064f\u0642\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0645\u0650\u0631\u064d \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19388,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/06\/21\/pardon-hudud-if-possible\/","url_meta":{"origin":25273,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Hudud: Pardon criminal before notifying ruler, if possible","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 21, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Amr reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cPardon the legal punishments between yourselves, for whatever offense reaches me must be punished.\u201d Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 4376 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0645\u0652\u0631\u0650\u0648 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0627\u0635\u0650 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":9815,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/11\/15\/riddah-murtad-pardon\/","url_meta":{"origin":25273,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Riddah: The Prophet pardons an apostate traitor","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 15, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: Abdullah ibn Sa\u2019d ibn Abi Sarh would write for the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, but the devil deceived him and he joined the unbelievers. The Prophet ordered that he should be killed on the day of liberation, but Uthman ibn Affan sought\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":2873,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/04\/12\/prophet-always-recommends-forgiveness\/","url_meta":{"origin":25273,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Pardon: The Prophet always recommended forgiveness","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 12, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: I never saw a case involving legal retaliation being referred to the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, but that he would command pardoning the criminal. Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 449